The leaders of Australia, India, Japan, and the United States gathered in Hiroshima to reaffirm their commitment to the Quad, a partnership aimed at promoting a free and open Indo-Pacific region. They envision a peaceful and prosperous region where countries can cooperate and trade based on partnership and mutual respect. They believe that engaging openly and transparently creates more opportunities and economic vitality. They aim to contribute to the resilience and prosperity of the Indo-Pacific by leveraging their resources and expertise. They also emphasize the principles of sovereignty and territorial integrity. They will work together to find common solutions for the region's challenges, such as health security, rapidly changing technology, climate change, and strategic challenges.